%N A275908 Expansion of (1+2*x+4*x^2+4*x^3+6*x^4+4*x^5+x^6) / (1-3*x-x^2-6*x^3-7*x^4-7*x^5-5*x^6-x^7).
%C A275908 Number of maximal matchings in a graph composed of a zig-zag chain with n hexagons. This is the graph Z_n shown in the Doslic and Short reference in figure 4, and also illustrated in the Examples. - _Andrew Howroyd_, Jul 21 2026
%H A275908 Colin Barker, <a href="/A275908/b275908.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..1000</a>
%H A275908 T. Doslic and T. Short, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/1511.00590">Maximal matchings in polyspiro and benzenoid chains</a>, arXiv:1511.00590, [math.CO], 2015. See Th. 4.4.
%H A275908 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/MaximalIndependentEdgeSet.html">Maximal Independent Edge Set</a>.
%H A275908 <a href="/index/Rec#order_07">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (3,1,6,7,7,5,1).
%F A275908 a(n) = 3*a(n-1) + a(n-2) + 6*a(n-3) + 7*a(n-4) + 7*a(n-5) + 5*a(n-6) + a(n-7) for n>6. - _Colin Barker_, Aug 26 2016
%e A275908 From _Andrew Howroyd_, Jul 21 2026: (Start)
%e A275908 Illustration of the graph for n = 4:
%e A275908        o----o        o----o
%e A275908       /      \      /      \
%e A275908      o        o----o        o----o
%e A275908       \      /      \      /      \
%e A275908        o----o        o----o        o
%e A275908              \      /      \      /
%e A275908               o----o        o----o
%e A275908 (End)
%t A275908 CoefficientList[Series[(1+2x+4x^2+4x^3+6x^4+4x^5+x^6)/(1-3x-x^2-6x^3- 7x^4- 7x^5-5x^6-x^7),{x,0,30}],x] (* _Harvey P. Dale_, Mar 08 2023 *)
%t A275908 (* Alternative: *)
%t A275908 LinearRecurrence[{3,1,6,7,7,5,1},{1,5,20,75,288,1105,4234},30] (* _Harvey P. Dale_, Mar 08 2023 *)
%o A275908 (PARI) Vec((1+2*x+4*x^2+4*x^3+6*x^4+4*x^5+x^6)/(1-3*x-x^2-6*x^3- 7*x^4-7*x^5-5*x^6-x^7) + O(x^30)) \\ _Colin Barker_, Aug 26 2016
